in css:

    .table {
      border-collapse: collapse;
      border-style: hidden;
    }
    
    .cell {
      padding: 5px 10px;
    }
    
    .row:nth-of-type(1n+1) {
      border-bottom: 2px solid pink; 
    }
    
    .cell:nth-of-type(2n-1) {
      border-right: 2px solid pink;  
    }

Explanation:

Just skip first row to set top border:

    .row:nth-of-type(1n+1) {
          border-bottom: 2px solid pink; 
    }

and then, set border only to odd cells:

    .cell:nth-of-type(2n-1) {
          border-right: 2px solid pink;  
    }


